---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'March 5, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use — Matrix Digital Media"
  description="Terms of use for all apps published by Matrix Digital Media LLC."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="policy-page">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="policy-header">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">← Home</a>
        <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="meta">Matrix Digital Media LLC &mdash; Last updated {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-body">

        <p class="intro">
          These Terms of Use govern your use of all mobile applications and digital products
          published by <strong>Matrix Digital Media LLC</strong> ("we," "us," or "our"),
          including HiveHelper and any future apps. By downloading or using our apps, you agree
          to these terms. If you do not agree, do not use our apps.
        </p>

        <section>
          <h2>1. License</h2>
          <p>
            We grant you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to
            download and use our apps on devices you own or control, solely for your personal,
            non-commercial purposes, subject to these terms.
          </p>
          <p>
            You may not copy, modify, distribute, sell, or lease any part of our apps, nor may
            you reverse engineer or attempt to extract the source code, except where applicable
            law prohibits this restriction.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. Accounts</h2>
          <p>
            Some features require you to create an account. You are responsible for maintaining
            the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activity that occurs
            under your account.
          </p>
          <p>
            You may request deletion of your account at any time from within the app. Account
            deletion permanently removes your data from our systems. This action cannot be undone.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. Subscriptions and Purchases</h2>
          <p>
            Some features are available only with a paid subscription. Subscriptions are offered
            on a monthly or annual basis and are billed through your Apple ID via the App Store.
          </p>
          <p>
            Subscriptions automatically renew at the end of each billing period unless cancelled
            at least 24 hours before the renewal date. You can manage or cancel your subscription
            at any time through your Apple ID subscription settings.
          </p>
          <p>
            All payments are processed by Apple. We do not receive or store your payment details.
            Refunds are handled in accordance with
            <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/us/terms.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              Apple's purchase terms
            </a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Free trials, where offered, convert to paid subscriptions at the end of the trial
            period unless cancelled beforehand. The trial duration and applicable pricing are
            displayed at the time of sign-up.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Your Content</h2>
          <p>
            Our apps allow you to create and store content such as inspection logs, notes, and
            photos ("Your Content"). You retain ownership of Your Content.
          </p>
          <p>
            By using features that transmit Your Content to third-party services (such as AI
            guidance), you grant those services the rights necessary to process Your Content
            to fulfill the feature. This is described in our
            <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            You are solely responsible for the accuracy of the content you enter. Our apps are
            tools to assist you — they are not a substitute for professional veterinary, agricultural,
            or beekeeping advice.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. Prohibited Uses</h2>
          <p>You agree not to use our apps to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Violate any applicable law or regulation</li>
            <li>Infringe the intellectual property rights of any party</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any system or network</li>
            <li>Interfere with or disrupt the integrity or performance of our apps or services</li>
            <li>Use automated means to access or collect data from our apps without our permission</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. AI Features</h2>
          <p>
            Certain features use third-party AI services to generate guidance or analysis based
            on data you provide. AI-generated content is provided for informational purposes only
            and may not always be accurate, complete, or appropriate for your specific situation.
          </p>
          <p>
            We do not warrant the accuracy or reliability of AI-generated output. You should
            independently verify any guidance before acting on it, especially for decisions
            that affect your hives, health, or property.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
          <p>
            Our apps are provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind,
            either express or implied, including but not limited to implied warranties of
            merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement.
          </p>
          <p>
            We do not warrant that our apps will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of
            viruses or other harmful components. We make no warranty regarding the accuracy
            or reliability of any content or results generated by the apps.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, Matrix Digital Media LLC shall not be liable
            for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including
            but not limited to loss of data, loss of profits, or loss of goodwill, arising out
            of or in connection with your use of our apps, even if we have been advised of the
            possibility of such damages.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our total liability to you for any claims arising from your use of our apps shall
            not exceed the amount you paid us in the twelve months preceding the claim, or
            fifty US dollars ($50), whichever is greater.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Termination</h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your access to our apps at any time,
            with or without notice, if we believe you have violated these terms or for any other
            reason at our discretion.
          </p>
          <p>
            You may stop using our apps at any time. Deleting the app from your device ends
            your use. To cancel a subscription, do so through your Apple ID settings before
            the next renewal date.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These terms are governed by the laws of the State of New Jersey, United States,
            without regard to its conflict of law principles. Any disputes shall be resolved
            in the courts of New Jersey, and you consent to personal jurisdiction in those courts.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>11. Changes to These Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms of Use from time to time. When we do, we will update the
            "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Continued use of our apps after changes
            are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions about these Terms of Use, please contact us at:<br />
            <a href="mailto:support@matrixnj.com">support@matrixnj.com</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            Matrix Digital Media LLC<br />
            New Jersey, United States
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .policy-page {
    padding-top: calc(var(--header-h) + 4rem);
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .policy-header {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link:hover { color: var(--text); }

  .policy-header h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .meta {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .policy-body {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem 1.25rem;
  }

  ul li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent-1);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  a:hover { opacity: 0.8; }

  strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
